
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a destination node's children collection. It uses an expression to specify the destination and retrieves nodes from a source using [get-nodes]. The [add] slot appends the retrieved nodes to the destination node's children collection.
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to a destination node's children collection.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the specified source expression.
 */
add:x:+/*
   get-nodes:x:@.body/*
